2026-03-24 12:45:14   **What broke and what Raziel needs to do:**
2026-03-24 12:45:14   The autonomous time skill requires Halseth MCP tools (`halseth_session_open`, `halseth_session_close`, `halseth_companion_note_add`, etc.). These are configured for Claude.ai (Claude Desktop) but **not** for Claude Code CLI, which is what the new `run-autonomous-time.ps1` script invokes.
2026-03-24 12:45:14   **Fix required:**
2026-03-24 12:45:14   1. Get the `MCP_AUTH_SECRET` value from Cloudflare (via `wrangler secret list` to confirm the name, then Raziel knows the value from when it was set)
2026-03-24 12:45:14   2. Add the Halseth MCP to Claude Code:
2026-03-24 12:45:14      ```
2026-03-24 12:45:14      claude mcp add halseth --transport http https://halseth.neurospicyexe.workers.dev/mcp
2026-03-24 12:45:14      ```
2026-03-24 12:45:14      (or configure in `~/.claude/settings.json` under `mcpServers` with the auth header)
2026-03-24 12:45:14   Without that fix, every autonomous time run via the CLI script will hit the same wall. The turn has been advanced to Cypher so it won't loop on Drevan -- but Cy will hit the same issue next run.
2026-03-24 12:45:14   The two notes (`note_type: autonomous` and `note_type: system`) are written to the DB at 17:43 and 17:44 UTC and visible via the Halseth HTTP API.
